                <script
                    type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Who is eligible to apply for the IIAT Lead Program?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The program is open to all ages who either own a business or are in the ideation phase. It is also ideal for corporate professionals seeking hands-on learning and able to attend weekend classes."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are there specific sectors that applicants must focus on?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, your venture or idea must align with one of the following sectors: Ed-tech, Fintech, Health-tech, D2C, or Clean Tech."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do I need prior entrepreneurial experience to apply?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No prior experience is necessary. The program is designed for individuals at various stages, from ideation to early-stage ventures and entrepreneurs who want to scale their business."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How can I apply for the program?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"You can apply by completing the online application form on our website. The application includes questions about your background, venture details, and reasons for joining the program."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When is the application deadline?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Please visit the program's official website for the most up-to-date application deadlines."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is there an application fee?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No, there is no fee to apply for the program."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What criteria are used to evaluate applications?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Applications are assessed based on the stage of your startup or idea, its alignment with the program's focus sectors, and your motivation for participation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are interviews or additional assessments part of the selection process?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Shortlisted candidates may need to go through profile evaluation"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are scholarships available?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, scholarships are offered and are determined based on the stage and potential of your startup, as evaluated during the application process."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the cost of the program?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The program fee for the IIAT Lead program is ₹4,25,000+ GST."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is the program fee refundable?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Fees once submitted for the IIAT Lead programme are non refundable. IIAT Hyderabad reserves the right to amend this refund policy at any time without prior notice."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is included in the cost of the program?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The program fee for IIAT Lead Program will cover the cost of:\n1) Tuition fees for the courses, workshops, retreats, and events.\n2) All dining excursions organised by the IIAT Lead team including breakfast, lunch, dinner, and snacks."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can applicants defer the admission offer from IIAT Hyderabad of business to next batch?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Currently, we are not offering the option to defer. Students who can't join the program in the current batch are advised to appear for selection in the next batch."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is the program conducted online or offline?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The IIAT Lead Program is a fully Hybrid Program held at the IIAT Campus in Hyderabad."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Will I receive a certificate upon completion?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, all students who successfully complete the program will be awarded a certificate of completion."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I apply if I'm not based in Hyderabad?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many students are selected per cohort?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Each cohort is carefully curated, with a maximum batch size of 40 students."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How long is the program?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The program runs for three months, offering an immersive, in-person learning experience."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is this program suitable for working professionals?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, the program is structured to accommodate corporate professionals who wish to accelerate their journey in entrepreneurship."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What tools and technologies will I learn in the program?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"You will become proficient in essential business tools including: Google Cloud Platform (GCP), Advanced Excel, Notion, Trello, Tableau, Python, Zapier, Power BI, Xero, Figma, Salesforce, Zoho Books, Discord, GitHub, GitLab, and Azure. These tools cover everything from project management and data analysis to product design and development."}}]}</script>
